  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Malawi Eye Health System Strengthening Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is a one-year project and will target 9 health facilities in the South West Zone (SWZ) and Lilongwe districts. There are no direct beneficiaries in the project however, after the health facility systems are strengthened, poor people from the remote areas, people with disabilities and women will benefit from biometry during cataract surgeries. The project aims to achieve its goal through provision of training, procurement of computers and eye health equipment for the health facilities, technical support, and advocacy.</narrative>
  </description>
